==== Dual Boot gentoo and FreeBSD ====

<!--T:42-->/etc/lilo.conf
To do so; you have to edit your `/etc/lilo.conf` :
<!--T:43-->
{{File|/etc/lilo.conf|Dual boot: Gentoo and FreeBSD|<pre>
large-memory
lba32
boot=/dev/sda
install=menu
map=/boot/map
prompt
 
default=Linux
image=/boot/vmlinuz-2.6.26
label="Linux"
root=/dev/sda1
append=""
read-only
optional
 
other=/dev/sda3
label="FreeBSD"
</pre>}}
